actual.comment:
To be updated at MTR.

1.A service contract entitled "Development and Demonstration of Wetland Ecosystem Evaluation Index System (EHI)" was awarded and is now in progress well and the draft report of this mission has been completed in June, 2015 and distributed to all six provincial projects for further comments; 

2.Hubei, Anhui and Hainan Projects have invited experts to do the EHI in their pilot PAs and fixed the baseline of their projects, The EHI has been used by Hainan Forestry department as one regular monitory tool in project pilot PAs and will be extended to other PAs in the whole Hainan Province (detail see the PIR report of Hainan Project); 

3. The rest of provincial projects have also planned related activity  in their work plan before MTR

Progress under this outcome goes well and several activities have been initiated:- 

1. A service contract entitled “Development of Guidelines for Infrastructure Development and Operation, and The Issuance of Official Guidelines for Fisheries, Aquaculture and Agriculture in and around Wetland PAs” was awarded and is in progress well and the achievements of this mission will make decision making reference for SFA and other agencies; 

2.SFA made great efforts to guide all the provinces to implement the “Wetlands conservation and management regulation” issued in early of 2013 to standardize the behavior of wetland use, containment of wetlands loss and damage.

3.SFA has reached a basic consensus with MEP,MOA, SOA, MWR and MLR on the issues of wetland conservation legislation and the " National Wetland Conservation Ordinance (Draft)" has been improved and submitted to state council and confidently expected to be issued within 2015; 

4.Project also make contribution to RAMSAR convention committee on technical and logistic support, etc.; 

5.Project has contribute to the wetland conservation and management related policies research taken lead by the State Council and the official announcement on strengthening wetland conservation and management will be issued within 2015;

An official announcement entitled “Further strengthening the construction of national wetland park ” has been issued by SFA in 2014 (No.6-2014)

baseline.comment:
